03/12/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU will finance a programme to control light weapons in Albania, ATA reported Thursday (2 December).
The 1.3m-euro programme will be implemented in 2005.
To date, the Union has provided 1.3 billion euros for different projects in Albania.
In other news, Albania and Germany signed a protocol for financial and technical co-operation, under which Germany will allocate 15.2m euros for electricity, water supply and environmental protection projects next year.
(ATA - 02/12/04)
